Note:
Runa Standard Library: Futures and Promises Module

Provides asynchronous computation primitives including futures, promises, and
async task management. Futures represent values that will be computed
asynchronously, while promises allow setting those values from producer
threads. Essential for non-blocking, reactive programming patterns.

Features:
- Future[T] for asynchronous value computation
- Promise[T] for setting future values from producers
- CompletableFuture[T] for manual completion control
- Future combinators (map, flatMap, filter, zip, etc.)
- Timeout support for all future operations
- Cancellation support with interruption handling
- Exception propagation and error handling
- Callback registration for completion events
- Thread pool integration for async execution
- Performance monitoring and execution tracking
- Integration with Runa's actor model
- Memory-efficient lazy evaluation

Future States:
- Pending: Computation not yet complete
- Completed: Successfully computed with a value
- Failed: Computation failed with an exception
- Cancelled: Computation was cancelled

Thread Safety: All future operations are thread-safe and designed
for concurrent access across multiple threads.
:End Note

Import "stdlib/concurrent/atomic" as atomic
Import "stdlib/concurrent/channels" as channels

Note: Core Future Types
Type called "Future" with T:
    state as String defaults to "pending"
    value as Optional[T] defaults to None
    exception as Optional[String] defaults to None
    completion_time as Optional[Float] defaults to None
    creation_timestamp as Float defaults to 0.0
    cancellation_requested as Boolean defaults to false
    callbacks as List[String] defaults to list containing
    dependencies as List[Future[Any]] defaults to list containing
    executor_context as Optional[Dictionary[String, Any]] defaults to None
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any] defaults to dictionary containing

Type called "Promise" with T:
    future as Future[T]
    completed as Boolean defaults to false
    creation_timestamp as Float defaults to 0.0
    completion_timestamp as Optional[Float] defaults to None
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any] defaults to dictionary containing

Type called "CompletableFuture" with T:
    state as String defaults to "pending"
    value as Optional[T] defaults to None
    exception as Optional[String] defaults to None
    completion_time as Optional[Float] defaults to None
    creation_timestamp as Float defaults to 0.0
    cancellation_requested as Boolean defaults to false
    dependent_futures as List[CompletableFuture[Any]] defaults to list containing
    callbacks as List[String] defaults to list containing
    executor_context as Optional[Dictionary[String, Any]] defaults to None
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any] defaults to dictionary containing

Type called "AsyncTask" with T:
    task_id as String
    function_name as String
    arguments as List[Any] defaults to list containing
    future as Future[T]
    priority as Integer defaults to 0
    creation_timestamp as Float defaults to 0.0
    start_timestamp as Optional[Float] defaults to None
    completion_timestamp as Optional[Float] defaults to None
    retry_count as Integer defaults to 0
    max_retries as Integer defaults to 0
    timeout as Optional[Float] defaults to None
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any] defaults to dictionary containing

Type FutureResult[T] is:
    | FutureSuccess with value as T and completion_time as Float
    | FutureTimeout with elapsed_time as Float
    | FutureCancelled with cancellation_reason as String
    | FutureException with error_message as String and error_code as String

Type PromiseResult[T] is:
    | PromiseCompleted with value as T and completion_time as Float
    | PromiseAlreadyCompleted with existing_value as T
    | PromiseException with error_message as String and error_code as String

Type TaskSubmissionResult is:
    | TaskSubmitted with task_id as String and estimated_completion as Float
    | TaskRejected with reason as String and queue_size as Integer
    | TaskException with error_message as String and error_code as String
:End Note

Note: Basic Future Operations
Process called "create_future" returns Future[Any]:
    Let current_time be get_current_timestamp
    
    Let future be Future[Any] with:
        state as "pending"
        value as None
        exception as None
        completion_time as None
        creation_timestamp as current_time
        cancellation_requested as false
        callbacks as list containing
        dependencies as list containing
        executor_context as None
        metadata as dictionary containing "created_by" as "future_factory"
    
    Return future

Process called "create_completed_future" that takes value as Any returns Future[Any]:
    Let current_time be get_current_timestamp
    
    Let future be Future[Any] with:
        state as "completed"
        value as value
        exception as None
        completion_time as current_time
        creation_timestamp as current_time
        cancellation_requested as false
        callbacks as list containing
        dependencies as list containing
        executor_context as None
        metadata as dictionary containing "created_by" as "completed_future_factory"
    
    Return future

Process called "create_failed_future" that takes error_message as String returns Future[Any]:
    Let current_time be get_current_timestamp
    
    Let future be Future[Any] with:
        state as "failed"
        value as None
        exception as error_message
        completion_time as current_time
        creation_timestamp as current_time
        cancellation_requested as false
        callbacks as list containing
        dependencies as list containing
        executor_context as None
        metadata as dictionary containing "created_by" as "failed_future_factory"
    
    Return future

Process called "future_get" that takes future as Future[Any] and timeout as Optional[Float] returns FutureResult[Any]:
    Let start_time be get_current_timestamp
    
    Try:
        Note: Check if already completed
        If future.state is equal to "completed":
            Return FutureSuccess with:
                value as future.value
                completion_time as future.completion_time
        
        Else If future.state is equal to "failed":
            Return FutureException with:
                error_message as future.exception
                error_code as "FUTURE_EXECUTION_FAILED"
        
        Else If future.state is equal to "cancelled":
            Return FutureCancelled with:
                cancellation_reason as "Future was cancelled"
        
        Note: Wait for completion
        Let wait_result be wait_for_future_completion with:
            future as future
            timeout as timeout
        
        Match wait_result.status:
            When "completed":
                Let completion_time be get_current_timestamp minus start_time
                Return FutureSuccess with:
                    value as future.value
                    completion_time as completion_time
            
            When "failed":
                Return FutureException with:
                    error_message as future.exception
                    error_code as "FUTURE_EXECUTION_FAILED"
            
            When "cancelled":
                Return FutureCancelled with:
                    cancellation_reason as "Future was cancelled during wait"
            
            When "timeout":
                Let elapsed_time be get_current_timestamp minus start_time
                Return FutureTimeout with elapsed_time as elapsed_time
            
            Otherwise:
                Return FutureException with:
                    error_message as "Unknown wait result: " plus wait_result.status
                    error_code as "FUTURE_UNKNOWN_WAIT_STATUS"
    
    Catch error:
        Return FutureException with:
            error_message as "Future get exception: " plus error.message
            error_code as "FUTURE_GET_EXCEPTION"

Process called "future_is_done" that takes future as Future[Any] returns Boolean:
    Return future.state is not equal to "pending"

Process called "future_is_cancelled" that takes future as Future[Any] returns Boolean:
    Return future.state is equal to "cancelled"

Process called "future_cancel" that takes future as Future[Any] and may_interrupt as Boolean returns Boolean:
    If future.state is not equal to "pending":
        Return false  Note: Already completed or cancelled
    
    Try:
        Set future.cancellation_requested to true
        
        If may_interrupt:
            Let interrupt_result be interrupt_future_execution with future as future
            If not interrupt_result.success:
                Note: Could not interrupt, but still mark as cancelled
                Set future.state to "cancelled"
                Set future.completion_time to get_current_timestamp
                Let notify_result be notify_future_callbacks with future as future
                Return true
        
        Set future.state to "cancelled"
        Set future.completion_time to get_current_timestamp
        
        Note: Notify callbacks
        Let notify_result be notify_future_callbacks with future as future
        
        Return true
    
    Catch error:
        Return false

Process called "future_add_callback" that takes future as Future[Any] and callback_name as String returns None:
    Add callback_name to future.callbacks
    
    Note: If future is already completed, execute callback immediately
    If future.state is not equal to "pending":
        Let execute_result be execute_future_callback with:
            callback_name as callback_name
            future as future
    
    Return None
:End Note

Note: Promise Operations
Process called "create_promise" returns Promise[Any]:
    Let current_time be get_current_timestamp
    Let future be create_future
    
    Let promise be Promise[Any] with:
        future as future
        completed as false
        creation_timestamp as current_time
        completion_timestamp as None
        metadata as dictionary containing "created_by" as "promise_factory"
    
    Return promise

Process called "promise_set_value" that takes promise as Promise[Any] and value as Any returns PromiseResult[Any]:
    If promise.completed:
        Return PromiseAlreadyCompleted with existing_value as promise.future.value
    
    Try:
        Set promise.completed to true
        Set promise.completion_timestamp to get_current_timestamp
        Set promise.future.state to "completed"
        Set promise.future.value to value
        Set promise.future.completion_time to get_current_timestamp
        
        Note: Notify all waiting threads and callbacks
        Let notify_result be notify_future_completion with future as promise.future
        If not notify_result.success:
            Return PromiseException with:
                error_message as "Failed to notify future completion: " plus notify_result.error_message
                error_code as "PROMISE_NOTIFICATION_FAILED"
        
        Return PromiseCompleted with:
            value as value
            completion_time as promise.completion_timestamp
    
    Catch error:
        Return PromiseException with:
            error_message as "Promise set value exception: " plus error.message
            error_code as "PROMISE_SET_VALUE_EXCEPTION"

Process called "promise_set_exception" that takes promise as Promise[Any] and error_message as String returns PromiseResult[Any]:
    If promise.completed:
        Return PromiseAlreadyCompleted with existing_value as promise.future.value
    
    Try:
        Set promise.completed to true
        Set promise.completion_timestamp to get_current_timestamp
        Set promise.future.state to "failed"
        Set promise.future.exception to error_message
        Set promise.future.completion_time to get_current_timestamp
        
        Note: Notify all waiting threads and callbacks
        Let notify_result be notify_future_completion with future as promise.future
        If not notify_result.success:
            Return PromiseException with:
                error_message as "Failed to notify future failure: " plus notify_result.error_message
                error_code as "PROMISE_FAILURE_NOTIFICATION_FAILED"
        
        Return PromiseCompleted with:
            value as None
            completion_time as promise.completion_timestamp
    
    Catch error:
        Return PromiseException with:
            error_message as "Promise set exception error: " plus error.message
            error_code as "PROMISE_SET_EXCEPTION_ERROR"

Process called "promise_get_future" that takes promise as Promise[Any] returns Future[Any]:
    Return promise.future

Process called "promise_is_completed" that takes promise as Promise[Any] returns Boolean:
    Return promise.completed
:End Note

Note: Completable Future Operations
Process called "create_completable_future" returns CompletableFuture[Any]:
    Let current_time be get_current_timestamp
    
    Let completable_future be CompletableFuture[Any] with:
        state as "pending"
        value as None
        exception as None
        completion_time as None
        creation_timestamp as current_time
        cancellation_requested as false
        dependent_futures as list containing
        callbacks as list containing
        executor_context as None
        metadata as dictionary containing "created_by" as "completable_future_factory"
    
    Return completable_future

Process called "completable_future_complete" that takes future as CompletableFuture[Any] and value as Any returns Boolean:
    If future.state is not equal to "pending":
        Return false  Note: Already completed
    
    Try:
        Set future.state to "completed"
        Set future.value to value
        Set future.completion_time to get_current_timestamp
        
        Note: Complete dependent futures
        Let complete_dependents_result be complete_dependent_futures with future as future
        
        Note: Notify callbacks
        Let notify_result be notify_completable_future_callbacks with future as future
        
        Return true
    
    Catch error:
        Return false

Process called "completable_future_complete_exceptionally" that takes future as CompletableFuture[Any] and error_message as String returns Boolean:
    If future.state is not equal to "pending":
        Return false  Note: Already completed
    
    Try:
        Set future.state to "failed"
        Set future.exception to error_message
        Set future.completion_time to get_current_timestamp
        
        Note: Fail dependent futures
        Let fail_dependents_result be fail_dependent_futures with:
            future as future
            error_message as error_message
        
        Note: Notify callbacks
        Let notify_result be notify_completable_future_callbacks with future as future
        
        Return true
    
    Catch error:
        Return false

Process called "completable_future_then_apply" that takes future as CompletableFuture[Any] and function_name as String returns CompletableFuture[Any]:
    Let dependent_future be create_completable_future
    Add dependent_future to future.dependent_futures
    
    Note: If future is already completed, apply function immediately
    If future.state is equal to "completed":
        Let apply_result be apply_function_to_value with:
            function_name as function_name
            value as future.value
        
        If apply_result.success:
            Let complete_result be completable_future_complete with:
                future as dependent_future
                value as apply_result.result
        Otherwise:
            Let fail_result be completable_future_complete_exceptionally with:
                future as dependent_future
                error_message as apply_result.error_message
    
    Else If future.state is equal to "failed":
        Let fail_result be completable_future_complete_exceptionally with:
            future as dependent_future
            error_message as future.exception
    
    Return dependent_future

Process called "completable_future_then_accept" that takes future as CompletableFuture[Any] and consumer_name as String returns CompletableFuture[Any]:
    Let dependent_future be create_completable_future
    Add dependent_future to future.dependent_futures
    
    Note: If future is already completed, apply consumer immediately
    If future.state is equal to "completed":
        Let accept_result be apply_consumer_to_value with:
            consumer_name as consumer_name
            value as future.value
        
        If accept_result.success:
            Let complete_result be completable_future_complete with:
                future as dependent_future
                value as None  Note: Consumers don't return values
        Otherwise:
            Let fail_result be completable_future_complete_exceptionally with:
                future as dependent_future
                error_message as accept_result.error_message
    
    Else If future.state is equal to "failed":
        Let fail_result be completable_future_complete_exceptionally with:
            future as dependent_future
            error_message as future.exception
    
    Return dependent_future

Process called "completable_future_then_run" that takes future as CompletableFuture[Any] and action_name as String returns CompletableFuture[Any]:
    Let dependent_future be create_completable_future
    Add dependent_future to future.dependent_futures
    
    Note: If future is already completed, run action immediately
    If future.state is equal to "completed":
        Let run_result be execute_action with action_name as action_name
        
        If run_result.success:
            Let complete_result be completable_future_complete with:
                future as dependent_future
                value as None
        Otherwise:
            Let fail_result be completable_future_complete_exceptionally with:
                future as dependent_future
                error_message as run_result.error_message
    
    Else If future.state is equal to "failed":
        Let fail_result be completable_future_complete_exceptionally with:
            future as dependent_future
            error_message as future.exception
    
    Return dependent_future

Process called "completable_future_exceptionally" that takes future as CompletableFuture[Any] and handler_name as String returns CompletableFuture[Any]:
    Let dependent_future be create_completable_future
    Add dependent_future to future.dependent_futures
    
    Note: If future is already completed
    If future.state is equal to "completed":
        Note: No exception, just pass through the value
        Let complete_result be completable_future_complete with:
            future as dependent_future
            value as future.value
    
    Else If future.state is equal to "failed":
        Note: Handle the exception
        Let handle_result be handle_exception_with_function with:
            handler_name as handler_name
            exception_message as future.exception
        
        If handle_result.success:
            Let complete_result be completable_future_complete with:
                future as dependent_future
                value as handle_result.result
        Otherwise:
            Let fail_result be completable_future_complete_exceptionally with:
                future as dependent_future
                error_message as handle_result.error_message
    
    Return dependent_future
:End Note

Note: Async Task Management
Process called "create_async_task" that takes function_name as String and arguments as List[Any] and priority as Optional[Integer] returns AsyncTask[Any]:
    Let current_time be get_current_timestamp
    Let task_id be generate_task_id
    Let final_priority be priority if priority is not None else 0
    
    Let future be create_future
    
    Let async_task be AsyncTask[Any] with:
        task_id as task_id
        function_name as function_name
        arguments as arguments
        future as future
        priority as final_priority
        creation_timestamp as current_time
        start_timestamp as None
        completion_timestamp as None
        retry_count as 0
        max_retries as 0
        timeout as None
        metadata as dictionary containing "created_by" as "async_task_factory"
    
    Return async_task

Process called "submit_async_task" that takes task as AsyncTask[Any] and executor_context as Optional[Dictionary[String, Any]] returns TaskSubmissionResult:
    Try:
        Let submission_result be submit_task_to_executor with:
            task as task
            executor_context as executor_context
        
        If submission_result.success:
            Set task.start_timestamp to get_current_timestamp
            Set task.future.executor_context to executor_context
            
            Return TaskSubmitted with:
                task_id as task.task_id
                estimated_completion as submission_result.estimated_completion
        Otherwise:
            Return TaskRejected with:
                reason as submission_result.rejection_reason
                queue_size as submission_result.queue_size
    
    Catch error:
        Return TaskException with:
            error_message as "Task submission exception: " plus error.message
            error_code as "TASK_SUBMISSION_EXCEPTION"

Process called "await_async_task" that takes task as AsyncTask[Any] and timeout as Optional[Float] returns FutureResult[Any]:
    Return future_get with future as task.future and timeout as timeout

Process called "cancel_async_task" that takes task as AsyncTask[Any] and may_interrupt as Boolean returns Boolean:
    Return future_cancel with future as task.future and may_interrupt as may_interrupt

Process called "get_async_task_status" that takes task as AsyncTask[Any] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Return dictionary containing:
        "task_id" as task.task_id
        "state" as task.future.state
        "creation_timestamp" as task.creation_timestamp
        "start_timestamp" as task.start_timestamp
        "completion_timestamp" as task.completion_timestamp
        "retry_count" as task.retry_count
        "is_done" as future_is_done with future as task.future
        "is_cancelled" as future_is_cancelled with future as task.future
:End Note

Note: Future Combinators
Process called "combine_futures" that takes futures as List[Future[Any]] returns Future[List[Any]]:
    Let combined_future be create_future
    
    If length of futures is equal to 0:
        Let complete_result be complete_future_with_value with:
            future as combined_future
            value as list containing
        Return combined_future
    
    Note: Check if all futures are already completed
    Let all_completed be true
    Let results be list containing
    
    For each future in futures:
        If future.state is equal to "completed":
            Add future.value to results
        Else If future.state is equal to "failed":
            Let fail_result be complete_future_with_exception with:
                future as combined_future
                error_message as "Combined future failed: " plus future.exception
            Return combined_future
        Else If future.state is equal to "cancelled":
            Let cancel_result be cancel_future_with_reason with:
                future as combined_future
                reason as "Combined future cancelled"
            Return combined_future
        Otherwise:
            Set all_completed to false
    
    If all_completed:
        Let complete_result be complete_future_with_value with:
            future as combined_future
            value as results
        Return combined_future
    
    Note: Set up completion tracking for pending futures
    Let completion_tracker be create_completion_tracker with:
        target_future as combined_future
        source_futures as futures
    
    Return combined_future

Process called "any_of_futures" that takes futures as List[Future[Any]] returns Future[Any]:
    Let any_future be create_future
    
    If length of futures is equal to 0:
        Let fail_result be complete_future_with_exception with:
            future as any_future
            error_message as "Cannot wait for any of zero futures"
        Return any_future
    
    Note: Check if any future is already completed
    For each future in futures:
        If future.state is equal to "completed":
            Let complete_result be complete_future_with_value with:
                future as any_future
                value as future.value
            Return any_future
        Else If future.state is equal to "failed":
            Note: Continue checking other futures
            Continue
    
    Note: Set up first-completion tracking
    Let first_completion_tracker be create_first_completion_tracker with:
        target_future as any_future
        source_futures as futures
    
    Return any_future

Process called "future_map" that takes future as Future[Any] and function_name as String returns Future[Any]:
    Let mapped_future be create_future
    
    If future.state is equal to "completed":
        Let map_result be apply_function_to_value with:
            function_name as function_name
            value as future.value
        
        If map_result.success:
            Let complete_result be complete_future_with_value with:
                future as mapped_future
                value as map_result.result
        Otherwise:
            Let fail_result be complete_future_with_exception with:
                future as mapped_future
                error_message as map_result.error_message
    
    Else If future.state is equal to "failed":
        Let fail_result be complete_future_with_exception with:
            future as mapped_future
            error_message as future.exception
    
    Else If future.state is equal to "cancelled":
        Let cancel_result be cancel_future_with_reason with:
            future as mapped_future
            reason as "Source future was cancelled"
    
    Otherwise:
        Note: Set up mapping for when future completes
        Let map_callback be create_map_callback with:
            target_future as mapped_future
            function_name as function_name
        
        Let add_result be future_add_callback with:
            future as future
            callback_name as map_callback
    
    Return mapped_future

Process called "future_filter" that takes future as Future[Any] and predicate_name as String returns Future[Any]:
    Let filtered_future be create_future
    
    If future.state is equal to "completed":
        Let filter_result be apply_predicate_to_value with:
            predicate_name as predicate_name
            value as future.value
        
        If filter_result.success and filter_result.result:
            Let complete_result be complete_future_with_value with:
                future as filtered_future
                value as future.value
        Else If filter_result.success:
            Let fail_result be complete_future_with_exception with:
                future as filtered_future
                error_message as "Future value did not pass filter predicate"
        Otherwise:
            Let fail_result be complete_future_with_exception with:
                future as filtered_future
                error_message as filter_result.error_message
    
    Else If future.state is equal to "failed":
        Let fail_result be complete_future_with_exception with:
            future as filtered_future
            error_message as future.exception
    
    Else If future.state is equal to "cancelled":
        Let cancel_result be cancel_future_with_reason with:
            future as filtered_future
            reason as "Source future was cancelled"
    
    Otherwise:
        Note: Set up filtering for when future completes
        Let filter_callback be create_filter_callback with:
            target_future as filtered_future
            predicate_name as predicate_name
        
        Let add_result be future_add_callback with:
            future as future
            callback_name as filter_callback
    
    Return filtered_future
:End Note

Note: Utility and Helper Functions
Process called "get_future_statistics" that takes future as Future[Any] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Let current_time be get_current_timestamp
    Let execution_time be None
    
    If future.completion_time is not None:
        Set execution_time to future.completion_time minus future.creation_timestamp
    
    Return dictionary containing:
        "state" as future.state
        "creation_timestamp" as future.creation_timestamp
        "completion_time" as future.completion_time
        "execution_time" as execution_time
        "is_done" as future_is_done with future as future
        "is_cancelled" as future_is_cancelled with future as future
        "callback_count" as length of future.callbacks
        "dependency_count" as length of future.dependencies
        "age_seconds" as current_time minus future.creation_timestamp

Process called "generate_task_id" returns String:
    Note: Implementation should generate unique task identifier
    Return "task_" plus get_current_timestamp as String

Process called "get_current_timestamp" returns Float:
    Note: Get current system timestamp in seconds since Unix epoch
    Return system_call_get_current_time_seconds


Note: Low-level Future Implementation Functions (Platform-dependent)
Process called "wait_for_future_completion" that takes future as Future[Any] and timeout as Optional[Float] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Wait for future to complete or timeout
    Return dictionary containing "status" as "completed"

Process called "interrupt_future_execution" that takes future as Future[Any] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Interrupt future execution if possible
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "error_message" as ""

Process called "notify_future_callbacks" that takes future as Future[Any] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Execute all registered callbacks
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "error_message" as ""

Process called "notify_future_completion" that takes future as Future[Any] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Notify all threads waiting on future completion
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "error_message" as ""

Process called "notify_completable_future_callbacks" that takes future as CompletableFuture[Any] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Execute all registered callbacks for completable future
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "error_message" as ""

Process called "complete_dependent_futures" that takes future as CompletableFuture[Any] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Complete all dependent futures
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "error_message" as ""

Process called "fail_dependent_futures" that takes future as CompletableFuture[Any] and error_message as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Fail all dependent futures with error
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "error_message" as ""

Process called "submit_task_to_executor" that takes task as AsyncTask[Any] and executor_context as Optional[Dictionary[String, Any]] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Submit task to thread pool executor
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "estimated_completion" as get_current_timestamp plus 5.0, "rejection_reason" as "", "queue_size" as 0

Process called "execute_future_callback" that takes callback_name as String and future as Future[Any] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Execute named callback function with future result
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "error_message" as ""

Process called "complete_future_with_value" that takes future as Future[Any] and value as Any returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Complete future with given value
    Set future.state to "completed"
    Set future.value to value
    Set future.completion_time to get_current_timestamp
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "error_message" as ""

Process called "complete_future_with_exception" that takes future as Future[Any] and error_message as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Complete future with exception
    Set future.state to "failed"
    Set future.exception to error_message
    Set future.completion_time to get_current_timestamp
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "error_message" as ""

Process called "cancel_future_with_reason" that takes future as Future[Any] and reason as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Cancel future with given reason
    Set future.state to "cancelled"
    Set future.completion_time to get_current_timestamp
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "error_message" as ""

Process called "apply_function_to_value" that takes function_name as String and value as Any returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Apply named function to value
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "result" as value, "error_message" as ""

Process called "apply_consumer_to_value" that takes consumer_name as String and value as Any returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Apply named consumer to value
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "error_message" as ""

Process called "execute_action" that takes action_name as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Execute named action
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "error_message" as ""

Process called "handle_exception_with_function" that takes handler_name as String and exception_message as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Handle exception using named handler function
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "result" as None, "error_message" as ""

Process called "apply_predicate_to_value" that takes predicate_name as String and value as Any returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Apply named predicate to value
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "result" as true, "error_message" as ""

Process called "create_completion_tracker" that takes target_future as Future[Any] and source_futures as List[Future[Any]] returns String:
    Note: Create tracker for multiple future completion
    Return "completion_tracker_" plus get_current_timestamp as String

Process called "create_first_completion_tracker" that takes target_future as Future[Any] and source_futures as List[Future[Any]] returns String:
    Note: Create tracker for first future completion
    Return "first_completion_tracker_" plus get_current_timestamp as String

Process called "create_map_callback" that takes target_future as Future[Any] and function_name as String returns String:
    Note: Create callback for future mapping
    Return "map_callback_" plus function_name

Process called "create_filter_callback" that takes target_future as Future[Any] and predicate_name as String returns String:
    Note: Create callback for future filtering
    Return "filter_callback_" plus predicate_name
:End Note